Achilles is the son of the military man Peleus and the sea-nymph Thetis. The most powerful warrior inThe Iliad,Achilles commands the Myrmidons, soldiers from his homeland of Phthia in Greece. Proud and headstrong, he takes offense easily and reacts with blistering indignation when he perceives that his honor has been slighted. Achillesâ€™ wrath at Agamemnon for taking his war prize, the maiden Briseis, forms the main subject ofThe Iliad.Read anin-depth analysis of Achilles.